headline: How the AB InBev Global Partnership Has Changed the Investment Narrative at Netflix (NFLX)
summary: On September 22, 2025, AB InBev and Netflix jointly announced a global partnership to combine AB InBev’s leading beer brands with Netflix’s popular entertainment platform, featuring co-marketing campaigns, title integrations, digital promotions, and advertising across live sports and events. This collaboration marks Netflix’s expanding focus on advertising and branded experiences, leveraging international partnerships to reach new audiences and strengthen non-subscription revenue...

headline: Netflix Stock Drops Again. Elon Musk Is Still Slamming the Streamer.
summary: Netflix  stock was down again on Thursday, amid a conservative backlash centered on the creator of an animated TV show.  Since Tuesday,  Tesla  CEO Elon Musk has been sharing and responding to X posts calling for people to boycott the streaming service.  “Same,” Musk wrote on X Tuesday, in response to a post where a user said they had canceled their Netflix subscription.
